commit.message: Fix another build warning
Use PKG_CHECK_MODULES to detect the libxml2 library
fix some build warnings
Use pkg-config to find FreeType (thanks to Lars Wendler).
fix incorrect use of AC_ARG_WITH

No longer automatically build with ImageMagick or GraphicsMagick if
present; now need to explicitly specify --with-imagemagick or
--with-graphicsmagick to configure
use different module names ImageMagick vs GraphicsMagick just to distinguish them in config log
merge MAGICK_CPPFLAGS into MAGICK_CFLAGS
try using simpler way of building with ImageEMagick

Looks like I need both MAGICK_CPPFLAGS and MAGICK_CFLAGS for GraphicsMagick
and ImageMagick.
fix to build with GraphicsMagick
change to interim version number
call this version 0.7.2
Require cell start and end times (if specified) to be nonempty
mention hinting change
enable hinting of rendered text
missing return from main in mpeg2desc

Fix inconsistency between MAGICK_CPPFLAGS being defined in configure,
and MAGICK_CFLAGS being used in Makefile.
mention last change in changelog
ensure that .BUP and .IFO files end up in different ECC blocks
mention new man page in ChangeLog

add video_format(7) man page

This documents the convention used by the DVDAuthor suite for
specifying the video format. This spec is also proposed as a common
convention for use by other programs that have to work with video.
use sprintf_alloc routine in a couple of troublesome places
add sprintf_alloc routine to help avoid fixed-length string buffers
allocate buffer dynamically to avoid overflow
schema updates
allow specification of provider field in VMG IFO file
mention some notable changes
don't force pause on last PGC cell to infinite

configure.ac: fix static build

Add LT_INIT macro to handle --enable-shared option.

If enable-shared=no then add --static flag to resolve FREETYPE_LIBS.

Otherwise, dvdauthor forget to link witk -lbz2 when linking with freetype2.

Fixes:
http://autobuild.buildroot.net/results/1d8/1d83390a3dd9f6bb595e9fc7b321500b4dc533a8/

Signed-off-by: Romain Naour <romain.naour@openwide.fr>
